description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Laundry Multi-Skilled Maintenance Technician&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Division: Corporate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care Group: Estates and Facilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band: 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: £24,907 - £30,615 per annum/pro rata&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: Week Commencing 9th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting for a &lt;strong&gt;Laundry Multi-skilled Maintenance Technician&lt;/strong&gt; having a Mechanical bias who shares our ambition and vision to deliver the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Best of Care by the Best People&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and has the drive to take us forward, by ensuring that the Trust continues to be the first choice for patients and our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to carry out planned preventative Laundry maintenance, inspections, testing, repairs and commissioning on a wide range of plant, equipment and services in accordance with Trust and Statutory procedures. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will also be required to undertake minor improvement and installation work across the Trust as directed. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants need to have had substantial post qualification experience and have served a recognised apprenticeship. The ability to fault find is essential. Experience working within the health service is not essential. You must be able to demonstrate cross trade multi-skilling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust and its employees are all committed to creating and maintaining a fair and supportive working environment and culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our commitment to you, we will give you the opportunity to utilise and enhance your talents to assist us in the development of shaping the future of Medway NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust offers a number of apprenticeships and training opportunities in Leadership and Management, Business Services, Finance, Accounting, Human Resources, Clinical Support Work, Research and Innovation, Nursing Associate and Assistant Practitioner alongside our in-house comprehensive clinical pathways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our hope is that our education pathways will play a key role in enabling you to challenge the practices of the past and build capability for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is committed to the protection of children, young people, their families and vulnerable adults accessing its services. Promoting the message that “safeguarding is everyone’s business” is vital to ensure our patients are protected and safe from abuse. To this end you must comply with Trust’s and the Kent and Medway Safeguarding Board’s policies on safeguarding children, young people and vulnerable adults.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our values are &lt;strong&gt;B&lt;/strong&gt;old, &lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;very Person Counts, &lt;strong&gt;S&lt;/strong&gt;haring and Open and &lt;strong&gt;T&lt;/strong&gt;ogether.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To contribute to our exciting future and become part of our team, apply today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leo McGregor-Davies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hospital Engineer (Mechanical)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;leo.mcgregor-davies@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
